Protests over federal immigration enforcement raids and President Donald Trump's move to mobilize the National Guard and Marines in Los Angeles are spreading nationwide. Demonstrations were held Wednesday in cities including Spokane and Seattle, Washington, and Las Vegas.

Protesters in Los Angeles are demanding an end to Trump's immigration crackdown, despite curfew and police response. (AP video: Mark Vancleave)

The California National Guard is conducting training on civil unrest in Los Alamitos, California, following several days of protests against immigration raids in Los Angeles. (AP video: Eugene Garcia)

