UFO's 1980 album, No Place to Run, will be reissued on CD and vinyl formats in August.

This album was produced by George Martin at AIR Studios in Montserrat and was the first to feature Paul Chapman on guitar, following the departure of Michael Schenker.

2CD and 3LP vinyl reissues feature newly remastered audio (courtesy of AIR Mastering) and include a recording of the UFO's appearance at The Marquee in London from 16 November 1980, newly mixed from the multi-track tapes, by Brian Kehew.

Both formats include notes by Michael Hann which incorporate interviews with Phil Mogg and Andy Parker. No Place to Run will be released on 15 August 2025, via Chrysalis Records.

