"https://news.google.com/rss/search?q=Supernatural","Syfy's New Supernatural Horror Show Adaptation Debuts To Strong Rotten Tomatoes Score","https://screenrant.com/revival-horror-show-rotten-tomatoes-score-debut/","Thu, 12 Jun 2025 16:20:00 GMT","

Syfy's new supernatural horror series, Revival, debuts Fresh on Rotten Tomatoes. Adapted from the Image Comics series of the same name created by Tim Seeley and Mike Norton, Syfy's Revival TV series is created by Aaron B. Koontz and Luke Boyce. Revival stars Melanie Scrofano, Romy Weltman, David James Elliott, and Andy McQueen, with Steven Ogg, Gia Sandhu, Karherine King, and WWE superstar CM Punk in recurring roles.

Revival debuted on Syfy on Thursday, June 12, and has received positive reviews on Rotten Tomatoes. Thus far, Revival is rated Fresh at 83% with 6 reviews. Revival season 1 will consist of 10 episodes, and the critics who have reviewed the series have been generally favorable, especially about series lead Melanie Scrofano, who plays police officer Dana Cypress. Check out Revival's Rotten Tomatoes score below:

Revival joins other popular recent hits on Syfy like Resident Alien and Chucky. Critics on Rotten Tomatoes hail Revival as ""a spiritual successor"" to Melanie Scrofano's prior series, Wynonna Earp, and praise Scrofano and the cast for elevating the series from its comic book roots. Revival also drew favor for ""not taking itself too seriously"" compared to other supernatural zombie series.

 Revival's cast led by Melanie Scrofano is a draw. Scrofano is also known for her recurring role in Star Trek: Strange New Worlds as Captain Marie Batel. One of Scrofano's Revival co-stars, Gia Sandhu, also plays T'Pring, the Vulcan fiancée of Spock (Ethan Peck), on Star Trek: Strange New Worlds. CM Punk, who also appeared in Netflix's wrestling drama Heels, brings his own fanbase, and Steven Ogg is a popular familiar face for his various roles in TV series like Snowpiercer and video games like Grand Theft Auto.

Revival's warm reception is great news for Melanie Scrofano, who stars in two shows in summer 2025. Along with Revival, Scrofano returns as Captain Batel in Star Trek: Strange New Worlds season 3. The back end of Revival's 10-episode season 1 will coincide with the first few weeks of Strange New Worlds season 3, which premieres on July 17 on Paramount+.

The Warrior Nun cancellation by Netflix after just two well-received seasons still stings, but one SyFy show could soothe the pain.

If Revival proves to be a hit that lasts a few seasons on Syfy, it takes some of the sting out of the announcement that Star Trek: Strange New Worlds is ending with season 5. Scrofano has amassed a solid and loyal fan base that has followed her since Wynonna Earp and its follow-up, Wynonna Earp: Vengeance. Revivial's strong start and Fresh Rotten Tomatoes score should help jumpstart it to become another mainstay for Syfy.

Source: Rotten Tomatoes

