Boulter will return to Nottingham next week, where she lifted the trophy in 2023 and 2024. With her ranking points already coming off, she feels she can swing freely again despite being the reigning champion there.

“Sitting here right now, I personally don't feel any pressure. I'm actually quite excited to go out and swing free now my points are off this week, so I've got nothing to lose from now,” she explained.

“It's not like I had a massive run in Wimbledon or in Eastbourne last year, so yeah, I can take a breath. I can enjoy it. I can enjoy playing now. And, you know, I'm on my favourite surface, I've got a great chance, I'm at my home tournament. I can swing free and, yeah, hopefully make a few more points.

“But honestly, like, I find that's not necessarily my focus. It really isn't. My focus is to keep improving my game, and to play matches like this today and start showing that I can beat people around that ranking, as well.”

